import React from "react"; import { evaluate } from 'mathjs'; export class Calculator extends React.Component{ constructor(props){ super(props); this.state = { calculate : '23', }; this.changeCalculate = this.changeCalculate.bind(this); } changeCalculate(e){ this.setState((prevState) => ({ calculate: prevState.calculate + ' + ' + e.target.value })); console.log(evaluate(this.state.calculate)); } sumTheNumbers(e){ this.setState((prevState) => ({ calculate: evaluate(prevState.state.calculate) })); console.log(this.state.calculate); } render(){ return(
{ this.state.calculate }
); } }
